g, and we have to ask them to repeat themselves multiple times. After the interview, I rejected all three candidates and so did the two other co-workers. Guess who says they passed the interview? Yup, an Indian female coworker. They were rejected. I met with the hiring manager and told her what happened. Instead of just replacing the Indian, they replaced the entire panel.", "author": "Tomis_4", "created": 1775400591290, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "BenDoverAssho", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "A few years ago, I was asked to interview a candidate for a PM role. It was a group interview and one of the job requirements is strong communication skills. Three Indians apparently passed the technical interview and the group interview is next. Ignoring the accent and broken English,", "last_comment_created": 1775403683681, "content": "<p>their responses to our questions are confusing, and we have to ask them to repeat themselves multiple times. After the interview, I rejected all three candidates and so did the two other co-workers. Guess who says they passed the interview? Yup, an Indian female coworker. They were rejected. I met with the hiring manager and told her what happened. Instead of just replacing the Indian, they replaced the entire panel.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 5, "score_up": 20, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid":